{
  "name": "Agent Memory — Session Save",
  "version": "6.0.0",
  "disabled": false,
  "description": "On agent stop: save meaningful session state to memory.md and playbook.md. Skip Q&A-only sessions.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[WORKSPACE GUARD: Only execute if the current session context involves files in 'VitProjects/' workspace. If the user is working exclusively in '.claude/' workspace, skip silently.] Session ended. Check if this session produced meaningful changes — defined as: new decisions made, files created/modified, phases completed, bugs fixed, or patterns discovered. If the session was ONLY Q&A, explanations, 'ทำต่อ', or 'approve' responses with no new artifacts → skip entirely and do NOT write anything. If meaningful changes occurred: 1) Update agent-memory/memory.md — Task_Ledger (max 5 entries, mark stale after 3 sessions), Decisions_In_Force (active decisions only), Recent_Lessons (last 5 IDs). 2) If a new reusable pattern was found (trigger + fix + domain) → append to agent-memory/playbook.md. 3) Report: 📝 Memory saved: [what changed] OR 📝 No memory changes (Q&A only)."
  }
}
